my new parakeet won't do anything i just got a yellow male parakeet today for my birthday and it won't do anything it won't drink the water or play with its toys or sing it just sits on the perch and looks miserable i got a book on parakeets and i fixed up the cage the way the book said to and he's not under a draft i don't know what's wrong is he lonely how can i make him a happy bird he is just getting new to his surroundings and he was probably with other birds at the pet store so he might be a little lonely i would put him in a quiet semi dark place and leave him be for a while until he adjusts to his new surroundings when he starts to perk up a bit just sit by the cage and talk to him in a quiet voice this will get him used to you don't rush things it is very tempting to try to start finger training them and playing with them immediatly when he's used to you try putting your hand in his cage for him to get used to it when he's used to it and its movements then try finger training birds are awesome if you invest time and lots of love in them you get great rewards good luck and congrats Shaggy dog story John Cage Salad Fingers Dog training Ferret Social rule RuneScape quests Hamster Kodocha Sin City The Beatles discography The Emancipation of Mimi Humphrey Bogart Garfield Wild at Heart (Buffy episode) Friends Budgerigar Eternal Sunshine of the Spotless Mind The Pet Sounds Sessions Customs and etiquette of Japan Aladdin (1992 film) Blood on the Tracks Fancy rat Parrot Canary Monk Parakeet Piccolo Junior Saga Care Bears Falconry Rich Mullins Mealy Parrot Treehouse of Horror V 2000 Australian Grand Prix Theory of conduct The Inside The Time Machine The Amber Spyglass The Human Stain She Loves You Time Out of Mind 1957 World Series Bong Skinny Puppy Yami to B__shi to Hon no Tabibito Gordon Banks Avenue Q Phoebe Buffay's songs Ron Weasley RuneScape locations Pok__mon Live! The Birds (film) Non-native pronunciations of English Red-masked Parakeet Hansel und Gretel Caro